<h3 class="govuk-heading-m">Find your login credentials</h3>

<ol class="govuk-list govuk-list--number govuk-list--spaced">
  <li>
    <strong>Open the CloudFormation console</strong>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      Go to <a href="https://us-east-1.console.aws.amazon.com/cloudformation/home?region=us-east-1#/stacks" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="govuk-link">CloudFormation console in us-east-1<span class="govuk-visually-hidden"> (opens in new tab)</span></a>
    </p>
  </li>

  <li>
    <strong>Find your stack</strong>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      Look for a stack containing <code>localgov-ims</code> in the name.
      The status should be <span class="govuk-tag govuk-tag--green">CREATE_COMPLETE</span>
    </p>
  </li>

  <li>
    <strong>Go to the Outputs tab</strong>
    <p class="govuk-body">Click the stack name, then select the <strong>Outputs</strong> tab. You'll see:</p>
    <table class="govuk-table">
      <thead class="govuk-table__head">
        <tr class="govuk-table__row">
          <th class="govuk-table__header">Output</th>
          <th class="govuk-table__header">What it is</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody class="govuk-table__body">
        <tr class="govuk-table__row">
          <td class="govuk-table__cell"><code>PaymentPortalUrl</code></td>
          <td class="govuk-table__cell">The citizen-facing payment portal URL</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="govuk-table__row">
          <td class="govuk-table__cell"><code>AdminPortalUrl</code></td>
          <td class="govuk-table__cell">The staff admin portal URL (for later steps)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="govuk-table__row">
          <td class="govuk-table__cell"><code>AdminUsername</code></td>
          <td class="govuk-table__cell">Admin login username</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="govuk-table__row">
          <td class="govuk-table__cell"><code>AdminPassword</code></td>
          <td class="govuk-table__cell">Admin login password</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </li>
</ol>

<h3 class="govuk-heading-m">Make a test payment</h3>

<ol class="govuk-list govuk-list--number govuk-list--spaced">
  <li>
    <strong>Open the payment portal</strong>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      Open the <code>PaymentPortalUrl</code> in a new tab. You'll see the citizen-facing payment page where residents can look up their account and make a payment.
    </p>
  </li>

  <li>
    <strong>Search for an account</strong>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      The seed data includes 200+ account holders. Try searching by:
    </p>
    <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
      <li><strong>Account reference</strong> — try <code>CT-001</code> for a Council Tax account</li>
      <li><strong>Name</strong> — try <code>Smith</code> to see matching residents</li>
    </ul>
  </li>

  <li>
    <strong>Select an account and enter a payment amount</strong>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      Select a Council Tax account from the results. You'll see the account balance and payment history. Enter a payment amount (for example, <code>150.00</code>) and click to proceed.
    </p>
  </li>

  <li>
    <strong>Complete the GOV.UK Pay checkout</strong>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      You'll be redirected to the GOV.UK Pay sandbox. This is a real GOV.UK Pay test environment. Use these test card details:
    </p>
    <table class="govuk-table">
      <thead class="govuk-table__head">
        <tr class="govuk-table__row">
          <th class="govuk-table__header">Field</th>
          <th class="govuk-table__header">Value</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody class="govuk-table__body">
        <tr class="govuk-table__row">
          <td class="govuk-table__cell">Card number</td>
          <td class="govuk-table__cell"><code>4444333322221111</code></td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="govuk-table__row">
          <td class="govuk-table__cell">Expiry date</td>
          <td class="govuk-table__cell">Any future date (e.g. <code>01/30</code>)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="govuk-table__row">
          <td class="govuk-table__cell">Name on card</td>
          <td class="govuk-table__cell">Any name</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="govuk-table__row">
          <td class="govuk-table__cell">Card security code</td>
          <td class="govuk-table__cell"><code>123</code></td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="govuk-table__row">
          <td class="govuk-table__cell">Billing address</td>
          <td class="govuk-table__cell">Any UK address</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="govuk-table__row">
          <td class="govuk-table__cell">Email</td>
          <td class="govuk-table__cell">Any email address</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </li>

  <li>
    <strong>Confirm payment success</strong>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      After completing the card details, you'll see the GOV.UK Pay confirmation page, then be redirected back to LocalGov IMS with a payment receipt. The transaction will now appear in the admin portal.
    </p>
  </li>
</ol>

<div class="govuk-inset-text">
  <strong>What you're seeing:</strong> This is the same GOV.UK Pay integration used by hundreds of councils across the UK. The sandbox environment processes test payments identically to production — the only difference is no real money moves. <a href="https://www.payments.service.gov.uk/" class="govuk-link">Learn more about GOV.UK Pay</a>.
</div>
